data.description: SELLERS ARE OFFERING A 2-1 MORTGAGE INTEREST RATE BUY DOWN  FOR BUYERS TO 6% -SEE FLYER IN DOCUMENTS TAB.  SELLERS HAVE AN ASSUMABLE 2.25%, 25YR VA LOAN, WITH A $422K BALANCE. IF VA BUYERS WOULD RATHER PURSUE THAT OPTION. Stately brick front, Expanded  4 bedroom, 2 full,  1  half bath Colonial, sited on a lovely tranquil corner lot, w/3 car driveway, concrete walkway, & rear patio for grilling, tanning/ entertaining. Significant addition completed in 2009,  adding a large primary bedroom ste w/cathedral ceiling, brilliant hardwood floors, framed by oversized  windows, a colossal walk in closet & convenient , practical , sun drenched home office w/ceramic tile flr & brick interior accent wall, which was the exterior wall from the existing house, prior to the addition. Within the last 5 yrs, the current owners completed a full remodel of the kit, powder rm, upper lvl full hallway bath, walk through closet in primary bedroom, installed a new closet in the front bedroom & installed new blinds throughout the home. As you enter the home, to the right, you enter a dining rm/ kitchen combo area w/a large dining area & recently ( August 2019) fully remodeled kitchen boasting elongated tile floor, granite counters, farmers sink, all new appliances, elegant pendant lighting , oven range, built in microwave, dishwasher, & refrigerator w/ ice-maker. The  cozy living rm features a natural gas fireplace w/mantel, 8 LED recessed lights & hardwood flooring. The living rm transitions to the Anderson Window lined sunroom through French drs. The sunroom also features a generous amount of recessed lighting & a rear door to the rear yard. Adjacent to the living rm is a quaint library/study w/built in shelving , hardwood flooring & a convenient entrance door to the front left side of the property. The ascending staircase  escorts you to the upper level featuring a guest bedroom with hardwood flooring, ceiling fan , and walk in closet. The remodeled full hallway bath  offers a soaking tub/shower combo, vanity and exhaust fan. Two additional bedrooms with hardwood flooring and the previously mentioned expanded addition round out the upper level.  The wall between  the middle bedroom and the primary bedroom is a non load bearing wall, which can easily be removed for a conversion of that middle bedroom into an additional full bathroom on the upper level. The  descending staircase  with three walled light sconces, ushers you to the finished lower level family/game room with berber carpet and windows which can offer multi-purpose functionality to the new owners. An exit door  leads to a walk up staircase offering a private alternate access for guests or a multi-generational living opportunity as there is a full bathroom opposite the finished living space. A large utility/storage area w/built in closets and shelving , washer, dryer, utility sink, sump pump and recently serviced ( 4 months ago) Gas Furnace and gas hot water heater, complete the lower level. Located a few blocks away from the Metro Station and plentiful retail shopping, this charming home wont last.  The Montgomery County Homeownership Assistance Fund (McHAF) helps MD homebuyers purchase a home in Montgomery County Highlights & Considerations • Down payment & closing cost assistance up to 40% of the household’s qualifying income, for a maximum second loan amt. of $25,000. • 0% interest rate deferred for 10 years then forgiven (conditions apply)*. • Can be combined with Mortgage Purchase Plan (MPP) Revolving Closing Cost Assistance Program (RCCAP/*5 for 5*) when borrower works in Montgomery County, MD. • Borrowers must meet all eligibility requirements established for Montgomery County Housing Opportunities Commission MPP and McHAF. • Available only to first time homebuyers. • Homebuyer education is required. This program has limited funding, so time is of the essence! Reach out today to Listing Agent for more info
